{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866450102,"sessionID":"ses_2861e289bffeEA9L147U2ruOXd","part":{"id":"prt_d79e3905e001cXa6H68ZveD3Bh","messageID":"msg_d79e29add001TaxM4zgsdMP1Oz","sessionID":"ses_2861e289bffeEA9L147U2ruOXd","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-14160eeeb2414713b7fcca9585a01803","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# CLI Build Command Design\n\n**AR**: AR-021 — CLI build 命令  \n**Module**: cmd/cli  \n**Language**: Python  \n**Size**: M\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `build` command is a core component of the AgentCube CLI that builds container images from packaged agent workspaces. It supports both local Docker builds and cloud-based builds, with automatic version management and comprehensive error handling.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐\n│   CLI (Typer)   │\n│  main.py     │\n└──────┬──────┘\n       │ build()\n       ▼\n┌─────────────────────┐\n│  BuildRuntime       │\n│  build_runtime.py   │\n└──────┬──────────────┘\n       │\n       ├──► MetadataService\n       │    └── load_metadata()\n       │    └── save_metadata()\n       │\n       └──► DockerService\n            └── check_docker_available()\n            └── build_image()\n            └── get_image_info()\n```\n\n### Key Components\n\n1. **CLI Layer** (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n   - Typer command definition\n   - User input validation\n   - Error handling and user feedback\n\n2. **Runtime Layer** (`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`)\n   - Build orchestration\n   - Version management\n   - Build mode selection\n\n3. **Service Layer**\n   - `MetadataService`: Metadata persistence and loading\n   - `DockerService`: Docker operations (build, push, etc.)\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### BuildOptions\n\nDictionary containing build command options:\n\n```python\n{\n    \"proxy\": Optional[str],          # Proxy URL for dependency resolution\n    \"cloud_provider\": Optional[str], # Cloud provider name (e.g., \"huawei\")\n    \"output\": Optional[str],         # Output path for build artifacts\n}\n```\n\n### BuildResult\n\nDictionary containing build output information:\n\n```python\n{\n    \"image_name\": str,       # Full image name with tag (e.g., \"agent:1.0.0\")\n    \"image_id\": str,         # Docker image ID (short form, 12 chars)\n    \"image_size\": str,       # Human-readable size (e.g., \"512.34 MB\")\n    \"size_bytes\": int,       # Size in bytes\n    \"build_time\": float,     # Unix timestamp of build completion\n}\n```\n\n### AgentMetadata Fields (Build-related)\n\nRelevant fields from `AgentMetadata` for build operations:\n\n```python\nagent_name: str              # Used as image name\nversion: Optional[str]       # Semantic version (auto-incremented)\nbuild_mode: str              # \"local\" or \"cloud\"\nimage: Optional[Dict[str, Any]]  # Build result storage\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### BuildRuntime.build()\n\n```python\ndef build(\n    self,\n    workspace_path: Path,\n    **options: Any\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Build a container image from a packaged agent workspace.\n\n**Parameters**:\n- `workspace_path` (Path): Path to the agent workspace directory\n- `options` (Dict[str, Any]): Build options including proxy, cloud_provider, output\n\n**Returns**: `BuildResult` dictionary\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Loads metadata from workspace\n2. Validates build prerequisites (Dockerfile exists, Docker available)\n3. Increments version (with rollback on failure)\n4. Executes build based on `build_mode` in metadata\n5. Updates metadata with build results\n6. Returns build result\n\n**Raises**:\n- `ValueError`: If Dockerfile not found or prerequisites not met\n- `RuntimeError`: If Docker is not available or build fails\n- `FileNotFoundError`: If metadata file not found\n\n### BuildRuntime._build_local()\n\n```python\ndef _build_local(\n    self,\n    workspace_path: Path,\n    metadata: AgentMetadata,\n    options: Dict[str, Any]\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Build image using local Docker daemon.\n\n**Parameters**:\n- `workspace_path` (Path): Path to workspace (used as build context)\n- `metadata` (AgentMetadata): Agent metadata containing name and version\n- `options` (Dict[str, Any]): Build options (proxy support)\n\n**Behavior**:\n- Constructs image name from `agent_name` and `version`\n- Optionally adds proxy build arguments if proxy provided\n- Delegates to `DockerService.build_image()`\n- Adds image name to result\n\n### BuildRuntime._build_cloud()\n\n```python\ndef _build_cloud(\n    self,\n    workspace_path: Path,\n    metadata: AgentMetadata,\n    options: Dict[str, Any]\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Build image in cloud provider (placeholder implementation).\n\n**Parameters**:\n- `workspace_path` (Path): Path to workspace\n- `metadata` (AgentMetadata): Agent metadata\n- `options` (Dict[str, Any]): Build options including cloud_provider\n\n**Behavior**:\n- Returns placeholder build result with cloud provider prefix\n- Logs cloud provider name\n\n### BuildRuntime._increment_version()\n\n```python\ndef _increment_version(\n    self,\n    workspace_path: Path,\n    metadata: AgentMetadata\n) -> str\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Increment agent version before build.\n\n**Parameters**:\n- `workspace_path` (Path): Path to workspace (for saving metadata)\n- `metadata` (AgentMetadata): Agent metadata to modify\n\n**Returns**: New version string\n\n**Version Rules**:\n1. **Semantic version** (X.Y.Z): Increment patch (Z)\n2. **Semantic version with prerelease** (X.Y.Z-N.suffix): Increment prerelease number (N)\n3. **Non-semantic version**: Append \".1\"\n4. **No version**: Set to \"0.1.0\"\n\n**Examples**:\n- `\"1.0.0\"` → `\"1.0.1\"`\n- `\"1.0.0-alpha.1\"` → `\"1.0.0-alpha.2\"`\n- `\"custom-version\"` → `\"custom-version-1\"`\n- `None` → `\"0.1.0\"`\n\n### BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites()\n\n```python\ndef _validate_build_prerequisites(\n    self,\n    workspace_path: Path\n) -> None\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Ensure workspace is ready for build.\n\n**Parameters**:\n- `workspace_path` (Path): Path to workspace\n\n**Checks**:\n1. Dockerfile exists at `{workspace_path}/Dockerfile`\n2. Docker daemon is available and running\n\n**Raises**:\n- `ValueError`: If Dockerfile not found\n- `RuntimeError`: If Docker not available\n\n### BuildRuntime._update_build_metadata()\n\n```python\ndef _update_build_metadata(\n    self,\n    workspace_path: Path,\n    metadata: AgentMetadata,\n    build_result: Dict[str, str],\n    tag: str = \"latest\"\n) -> None\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Store build results in metadata.\n\n**Parameters**:\n- `workspace_path` (Path): Path to workspace\n- `metadata` (AgentMetadata): Agent metadata to update\n- `build_result` (Dict[str, str]): Build result from DockerService\n- `tag` (str): Image tag (default \"latest\")\n\n**Behavior**:\n- Merges build result into `metadata.image` dictionary\n- Saves updated metadata to workspace\n\n### DockerService.build_image()\n\n```python\ndef build_image(\n    self,\n    dockerfile_path: Path,\n    context_path: Path,\n    image_name: str,\n    tag: str = \"latest\",\n    build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n) -> Dict[str, str]\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Build Docker image using Docker SDK.\n\n**Parameters**:\n- `dockerfile_path` (Path): Path to Dockerfile\n- `context_path` (Path): Build context directory\n- `image_name` (str): Base image name\n- `tag` (str): Image tag\n- `build_args` (Optional[Dict[str, str]]): Docker build arguments\n\n**Returns**: Dictionary with image_name, image_id, image_size, build_time\n\n**Behavior**:\n- Constructs full image name: `{image_name}:{tag}`\n- Calls `docker.from_env().images.build()`\n- Retrieves image information using `get_image_info()`\n- Adds build timestamp\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Hierarchy\n\n```\nException\n├── ValueError (User input errors)\n│   └── \"Dockerfile not found in workspace\"\n│   └── \"No metadata file found in workspace\"\n├── RuntimeError (System errors)\n│   └── \"Docker is not available or not running\"\n│   └── \"Failed to build Docker image\"\n│   └── \"Failed to log in to Docker registry\"\n│   └── \"Failed to tag Docker image\"\n└── FileNotFoundError\n    └── Metadata file not found\n```\n\n### Error Handling Strategy\n\n#### CLI Layer (main.py)\n\n```python\ndef build(...):\n    try:\n        runtime = BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n        result = runtime.build(workspace_path, **options)\n        console.print_success(result)\n    except Exception as e:\n        _handle_error(e, \"building image\", verbose)\n```\n\n#### Runtime Layer (build_runtime.py)\n\n```python\ndef build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    original_version = metadata.version\n    self._increment_version(workspace_path, metadata)\n    \n    try:\n        result = self._execute_build(...)\n        self._update_build_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, result)\n        return result\n    except Exception as e:\n        if original_version != metadata.version:\n            self._revert_version(workspace_path, original_version)\n        raise\n```\n\n#### Version Reversion on Failure\n\n- Store original version before increment\n- On build failure, restore original version\n- Log warning: \"Build failed, reverting version from X to Y\"\n- Save reverted metadata\n\n#### DockerService Error Handling\n\n```python\ndef check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n    try:\n        self.client.ping()\n        return True\n    except DockerException as e:\n        logger.warning(f\"Docker not available: {e}\")\n        return False\n\ndef build_image(self, ...):\n    if not self.check_docker_available():\n        raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n    \n    try:\n        image, build_logs = self.client.images.build(...)\n        return self.get_image_info(full_image_name)\n    except DockerException as e:\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to build Docker image: {e}\") from e\n```\n\n### User-Facing Error Messages\n\n| Error | Message | Exit Code |\n|-------|---------|-----------|\n| Dockerfile not found | \"Dockerfile not found in workspace. Run 'pack' first.\" | 1 |\n| Docker unavailable | \"Error building image: Docker is not available or not running\" | 1 |\n| Build failure | \"Error building image: Failed to build Docker image: {error}\" | 1 |\n| Metadata not found | \"Error building image: No metadata file found in {workspace}\" | 1 |\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### Test: BuildRuntime._increment_version()\n\n```python\ndef test_increment_semantic_version():\n    metadata = AgentMetadata(\n        agent_name=\"test\",\n        entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n        version=\"1.0.0\"\n    )\n    runtime = BuildRuntime()\n    new_version = runtime._increment_version(Path(\"/tmp\"), metadata)\n    assert new_version == \"1.0.1\"\n    assert metadata.version == \"1.0.1\"\n\ndef test_increment_prerelease_version():\n    metadata = AgentMetadata(\n        agent_name=\"test\",\n        entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n        version=\"1.0.0-alpha.1\"\n    )\n    runtime = BuildRuntime()\n    new_version = runtime._increment_version(Path(\"/tmp\"), metadata)\n    assert new_version == \"1.0.0-alpha.2\"\n\ndef test_increment_custom_version():\n    metadata = AgentMetadata(\n        agent_name=\"test\",\n        entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n        version=\"custom-version\"\n    )\n    runtime = BuildRuntime()\n    new_version = runtime._increment_version(Path(\"/tmp\"), metadata)\n    assert new_version == \"custom-version-1\"\n\ndef test_increment_no_version():\n    metadata = AgentMetadata(\n        agent_name=\"test\",\n        entrypoint=\"python main.py\"\n    )\n    runtime = BuildRuntime()\n    new_version = runtime._increment_version(Path(\"/tmp\"), metadata)\n    assert new_version == \"0.1.0\"\n```\n\n#### Test: BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites()\n\n```python\ndef test_validate_missing_dockerfile(tmp_path):\n    runtime = BuildRuntime()\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Dockerfile not found\"):\n        runtime._validate_build_prerequisites(tmp_path)\n\ndef test_validate_docker_unavailable(tmp_path, mocker):\n    runtime = BuildRuntime()\n    tmp_path.joinpath(\"Dockerfile\").write_text(\"FROM python:3.10\")\n    mocker.patch.object(runtime.docker_service, \"check_docker_available\", return_value=False)\n    with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"Docker is not available\"):\n        runtime._validate_build_prerequisites(tmp_path)\n```\n\n#### Test: BuildRuntime.build() - Version Reversion\n\n```python\ndef test_build_reverts_version_on_failure(tmp_path, mocker):\n    tmp_path.joinpath(\"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n        \"agent_name: test\\nentrypoint: python main.py\\nversion: 1.0.0\"\n    )\n    tmp_path.joinpath(\"Dockerfile\").write_text(\"FROM python:3.10\")\n    \n    runtime = BuildRuntime()\n    mocker.patch.object(runtime, \"_build_local\", side_effect=RuntimeError(\"Build failed\"))\n    mocker.patch.object(runtime.docker_service, \"check_docker_available\", return_value=True)\n    \n    with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n        runtime.build(tmp_path)\n    \n    metadata = runtime.metadata_service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n    assert metadata.version == \"1.0.0\"  # Reverted\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n#### Test: End-to-End Local Build\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.integration\ndef test_e2e_build_local(tmp_path):\n    # Create valid workspace\n    tmp_path.joinpath(\"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\")\n    tmp_path.joinpath(\"Dockerfile\").write_text(\"FROM python:3.10\\nCOPY main.py .\\nCMD python main.py\")\n    tmp_path.joinpath(\"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n        \"agent_name: test-agent\\nentrypoint: python main.py\\nversion: 1.0.0\"\n    )\n    \n    runtime = BuildRuntime()\n    result = runtime.build(tmp_path)\n    \n    assert result[\"image_name\"] == \"test-agent:1.0.1\"\n    assert \"image_id\" in result\n    assert result[\"image_size\"] != \"0.00 B\"\n    \n    metadata = runtime.metadata_service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n    assert metadata.version == \"1.0.1\"\n    assert metadata.image is not None\n```\n\n#### Test: Build with Proxy\n\n```python\ndef test_build_with_proxy(tmp_path, mocker):\n    tmp_path.joinpath(\"Dockerfile\").write_text(\"FROM python:3.10\")\n    tmp_path.joinpath(\"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n        \"agent_name: test\\nentrypoint: python main.py\"\n    )\n    \n    runtime = BuildRuntime()\n    build_mock = mocker.patch.object(runtime.docker_service, \"build_image\", return_value={\n        \"image_name\": \"test:latest\",\n        \"image_id\": \"abc123\",\n        \"image_size\": \"100 MB\",\n    })\n    \n    runtime.build(tmp_path, proxy=\"http://proxy.example.com:8080\")\n    \n    build_mock.assert_called_once()\n    call_args = build_mock.call_args\n    assert call_args.kwargs[\"build_args\"][\"HTTP_PROXY\"] == \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\"\n    assert call_args.kwargs[\"build_args\"][\"HTTPS_PROXY\"] == \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\"\n```\n\n### Mocking Strategy\n\n#### DockerService Mock\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_docker_service(mocker):\n    service = mocker.MagicMock(spec=DockerService)\n    service.check_docker_available.return_value = True\n    service.build_image.return_value = {\n        \"image_name\": \"test:1.0.0\",\n        \"image_id\": \"abc123def456\",\n        \"image_size\": \"512.34 MB\",\n        \"build_time\": 1234567890.0,\n    }\n    service.get_image_info.return_value = {\n        \"image_name\": \"test:1.0.0\",\n        \"image_id\": \"abc123def456\",\n        \"image_size\": \"512.34 MB\",\n        \"size_bytes\": 536870912,\n    }\n    return service\n```\n\n#### MetadataService Mock\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_metadata_service(tmp_path, mocker):\n    service = mocker.MagicMock(spec=MetadataService)\n    \n    def load_side_effect(path):\n        return AgentMetadata(\n            agent_name=\"test\",\n            entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n            version=\"1.0.0\",\n            build_mode=\"local\"\n        )\n    \n    service.load_metadata.side_effect = load_side_effect\n    service.save_metadata = mocker.MagicMock()\n    return service\n```\n\n### Test Coverage Goals\n\n| Component | Target Coverage |\n|-----------|-----------------|\n| build_runtime.py | 90%+ |\n| docker_service.py | 85%+ |\n| main.py (build command) | 80%+ |\n\n### Test Execution\n\n```bash\n# Run all tests\npytest tests/\n\n# Run with coverage\npytest --cov=agentcube.runtime.build_runtime --cov=agentcube.services.docker_service\n\n# Run integration tests only\npytest -m integration\n\n# Run unit tests only\npytest -m \"not integration\"\n```\n\n## CLI Usage\n\n### Basic Usage\n\n```bash\n# Build from current directory\nkubectl-agentcube build\n\n# Build from specific workspace\nkubectl-agentcube build -f /path/to/workspace\n\n# Build with verbose output\nkubectl-agentcube build --verbose\n\n# Build with proxy\nkubectl-agentcube build --proxy http://proxy.example.com:8080\n\n# Build with cloud provider\nkubectl-agentcube build --cloud-provider huawei\n```\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n1. Workspace must be packed (contains `Dockerfile` and `agent_metadata.yaml`)\n2. Docker daemon must be running (for local builds)\n3. Sufficient disk space for image storage\n\n### Output\n\n```\n⠋ Building image...\n✓ Successfully built image\n  Image name: test-agent:1.0.1\n  Image ID: abc123def456\n  Image size: 512.34 MB\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Required\n\n- `docker>=6.0.0`: Docker SDK for Python\n- `pydantic>=2.0.0`: Data validation (via AgentMetadata)\n- `pyyaml>=6.0.0`: YAML parsing (via MetadataService)\n\n### Optional\n\n- `kubernetes>=28.0.0`: Kubernetes support (for cloud builds)\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n1. **Multi-platform builds**: Support for `--platform` flag (linux/amd64, linux/arm64)\n2. **Build caching**: Layer caching optimization for faster builds\n3. **Parallel builds**: Support for building multiple workspaces concurrently\n4. **Build hooks**: Pre-build and post-build script execution\n5. **Cloud provider integrations**: Full implementations for AWS, GCP, Azure\n6. **Build metrics**: Detailed build time and size analytics\n7. **Build optimization**: Automatic dependency analysis and layer optimization","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py\">\nERROR [67:13] Argument of type \"float\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"value\" of type \"str\" in function \"__setitem__\"\n  \"float\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [99:27] Type \"float\" is not assignable to declared type \"int\"\n  \"float\" is not assignable to \"int\"\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py":[{"range":{"start":{"line":66,"character":12},"end":{"line":66,"character":36}},"message":"Argument of type \"float\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"value\" of type \"str\" in function \"__setitem__\"\n  \"float\" is not assignable to \"str\"","severity":1,"code":"reportArgumentType","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportArgumentType"}},{"range":{"start":{"line":98,"character":26},"end":{"line":98,"character":30}},"message":"Type \"float\" is not assignable to declared type \"int\"\n  \"float\" is not assignable to \"int\"","severity":1,"code":"reportAssignmentType","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportAssignmentType"}}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/design.md","time":{"start":1775866450092,"end":1775866450099}}}}
